v2.0.1 | Feb 24 2026:

  -- New Features --
[New] shared elog_lib (v1.0.0) integration: structured event logging with
      dual app/audit log model; eout() replaced with thin elog() wrapper
      preserving exact call signature; _lmd_elog_init() maps config vars to
      ELOG_* env vars; audit trail in /var/log/maldet/audit.log (root only);
      inode-preserving log truncation via elog_lib; dynamic log path sync
      for --user flag; fallback to direct write if elog_lib not loaded
[New] elog_event() calls at 11 operation points: config_loaded, scan_started,
      scan_completed, threat_detected, quarantine_added, quarantine_removed,
      file_cleaned, monitor_started, alert_sent; all guarded with command -v
      check for graceful degradation
[New] shared alert_lib (v1.0.1) integration: all email, Slack, Telegram,
      and Discord alerting primitives replaced with calls to shared library;
      _send_email, _json_escape, and inline Slack/Telegram blocks removed
[New] Discord alerting support: discord_alert and discord_webhook_url config
      variables; scan reports uploaded via Discord webhook multipart upload
[New] _lmd_alert_init maps LMD config vars to ALERT_* env vars and manages
      channel enable/disable state; called from prerun and monitor reload
[New] _lmd_dispatch_messaging provides single-call messaging dispatch to all
      enabled channels (Slack, Telegram, Discord) via alert_dispatch
[New] minimal messaging templates in internals/alert/ for Slack, Telegram,
      and Discord; scan report sent as file attachment, not template body
[New] native YARA scanning: scan_yara=1 enables YARA as an independent scan
      stage using the yara binary (or yr from YARA-X); supports custom rules
      via custom.yara and custom.yara.d/ drop-in directory for third-party
      rule sets; scan_yara_scope controls rule overlap with ClamAV YARA;
      compiled rules via yarac supported; hookscan passes scan_yara for
      ModSecurity upload scanning; import_custsigs_yara_url for remote rule
      import; preserved across upgrades; issue #392, #277, #239
[New] cron.watchdog weekly watchdog script for independent fallback signature
      updates when primary cron.daily is broken or stale; installed to
      /etc/cron.weekly/maldet-watchdog
[New] cron.daily explicit cPanel detection: parse /etc/userdatadomains for
      addon domain and subdomain document roots outside public_html;
      issue #268
[New] cron.daily Bitrix panel detection (/opt/webdir + /etc/nginx/bx);
      issue #381
[New] tlog_lib.sh shared library: multi-mode tracking (bytes/lines),
      atomic cursor writes, flock-based cursor locking, compressed rotation
      support (.xz/.bz2/.zst/.lz4), tlog_adjust_cursor() for mode-aware log
      trim; replaces 9 subprocess forks with in-process tlog_read() calls
[New] native batch scan engine: 43x faster end-to-end — real-world
      benchmark 1,217s → 28s on ~10,000 files (v1.6.6 → v2.0.1); batch
      grep -F Aho-Corasick hex matching with parallel workers replaces
      per-file Perl hexfifo.pl/hexstring.pl; eliminates per-file pattern
      compilation overhead; scan_workers controls worker count (default:
      auto = min(nproc, 4))
[New] ClamAV hex wildcard support (??, (aa|bb), *, nibble ?a/a?) for
      custom hex signatures in the native scanner
[New] batch parallel MD5 scanning via _md5_batch_worker(); Linux path uses
      xargs md5sum for single-process hashing, awk join replaces per-file
      grep for signature lookup; reduces ~100,000 subprocess forks to ~10
[New] internals.conf: column binary discovery ($coltest) with -o flag
      validation; enables hit list column formatting in email templates;
      CentOS 6 (util-linux 2.17) gracefully falls back to plain text

  -- Bug Fixes --
[Fix] messaging templates used %%SUBJECT%% token format instead of
      {{SUBJECT}} expected by alert_lib template engine; Slack, Telegram,
      Discord message text showed literal %%SUBJECT%% instead of subject
[Fix] genalert panel type dispatched messaging channels (Slack/Telegram/
      Discord), causing duplicate scan report delivery when both email_alert
      and email_panel_user_alerts were enabled; restrict messaging dispatch
      to file and digest alert types only
[Fix] install.sh: set alert/ template directory to 750; preserve custom.d/
      template overrides across upgrades
[Fix] panel email delivery no longer restricted to cPanel+sendmail; shared
      lib tries sendmail first then falls back to mail for any control panel
[Fix] import_conf() re-source compat.conf and syscnf after remote config
      so deprecated variable names in imported configs get mapped correctly
[Fix] guard $curl binary in ELK statistics (scan.etpl) and Telegram
      alerting (genalert) to prevent unbound-variable errors on systems
      without curl installed
[Fix] restrict custom signature file permissions to 640/750 when pubscan
      disabled; defense-in-depth alongside parent directory restrictions
[Fix] strip CR/LF from email subjects in _send_email() and panel alert
      path to prevent header injection
[Fix] replace hardcoded /var/tmp and cd /tmp with $tmpdir in hookscan.sh
[Fix] SysV init status() checks monitor.pid before pgrep fallback for
      reliable PID tracking
[Fix] Slack alerting: migrate from deprecated files.upload API to
      files.getUploadURLExternal + files.completeUploadExternal; fix
      multi-channel to use channels parameter instead of channel_id; check
      curl exit codes and verify "ok":true on all API calls; extract and log
      API error fields on failure; replace grep -oP with sed for portability;
      issue #458
[Fix] Telegram alerting: add missing /bot prefix before token in Bot API URL
      causing all alerts to fail; use $curl variable with -s flag and stderr
      redirect; check sendDocument exit code; issue #461
[Fix] Slack and Telegram alerts now fire in monitor mode digest/daily
      reports, not just single-file scan alerts; issue #387
[Fix] scan_stage_yara(): anchor dedup with end-of-field regex to prevent
      substring false-positives; deduplicate hits against scan_session for
      ClamAV+YARA overlap; per-file fallback (YARA < 4.0) uses sh -c wrapper
      to capture exit code through cpulimit; stderr filter handles YARA-X
      message format; clean() invokes scan_stage_yara() for post-clean
      verification; trap_exit()/clean_exit() clean up YARA temp files
[Fix] YARA rule validation: import_user_sigs() validates downloaded rules
      before installing; scan_stage_yara() validates compiled.yarc with test
      scan before use; malformed rules skipped with warning
[Fix] import_conf() remote config sourcing replaced with safe parser
      (_safe_source_conf) preventing remote code execution; config source
      order corrected to match documented loading order
[Fix] -co/--config-option: reject command substitution, semicolons, pipes,
      and shell metacharacters in config values
[Fix] hookscan.sh: validate filenames from ModSecurity inspectFile; reject
      shell metacharacters, non-printable characters, and non-existent files
[Fix] conf.maldet installed world-readable (0644) changed to 0640
[Fix] --user flag validates username (empty, path traversal, non-existent);
      restore() validates .info file paths (traversal, empty, non-existent
      dirs, non-root restores outside user home)
[Fix] monitor_check(): remove double ClamAV scan; clamd fatal errors no
      longer cause false quarantines; no longer launches engine with empty
      file list; YARA filter applied before scan; issue #454, #447, #459
[Fix] monitor_kill() guards empty $monitor_pid; monitor reload now sources
      compat.conf and sysconfig/default matching startup loading order
[Fix] 19 bare exit statements given explicit exit codes; unrecognized CLI
      arguments return exit 1; issue #366
[Fix] clean() operator precedence fixed with { } grouping; quarantine branch
      rescan uses clean_check=1; md5_hash typo corrected
[Fix] quarantine()/quar_hitlist(): TOCTOU mv exit code check; suspend_user
      ordering; $RANDOM replaced with file inode naming; quarantine.hist
      signature name in batch quarantine (-q); grep -F for literal matching;
      issue #399
[Fix] install.sh: man page compression on fresh install; backup find|xargs
      replaced with find -exec; backup mv exit code check; version gate
      removed (preserves data regardless of version); upgrade no longer kills
      inotify monitoring (systemctl restart); issue #414
[Fix] uninstall.sh: stop monitor before cleanup; remove orphaned man page
      and watchdog symlinks; clean sysconfig/default overrides and stale SysV
      artifacts; guard chkconfig with existence check
[Fix] FreeBSD detection: replace broken $OSTYPE == "FreeBSD" with cached
      os_freebsd using uname -s; all 9 dead code paths functional; id --user
      (GNU-only) changed to id -u (POSIX)
[Fix] clamselector() logs warning on clamd test failure instead of silently
      switching; no longer overwrites user scan_max_filesize; issue #452, #410
[Fix] cron.daily: flock lock leaked to backgrounded scans switched to
      CLOEXEC command form; overlapping runs prevented with flock lockfile;
      update failure logging was dead code (use PIPESTATUS[0]); issue #373
[Fix] cron.daily: remove LMDCRON=1 dead export (unused since 2014); replace
      flock '|| :' with exit code discrimination so config errors propagate
      to cron (inner errors exit 2, lock contention exits 1 → silent)
[Fix] cron.watchdog version update (maldet -d) now runs regardless of
      signature update result
[Fix] view_report() resolves "newest" and empty scan ID to most recent
      session; replace $EDITOR with cat for terminal output; issue #336
[Fix] panel alerts include signature name; rewrite hit parsing to while-read
      with BASH_REMATCH for paths with spaces; InterWorx guard against empty
      master_domain; issue #426
[Fix] tlog trim cursor unit mismatch: purge() and monitor_cycle()
      subtracted byte count (wc -c) from line-count cursor, producing
      garbage cursor values; replaced with tlog_adjust_cursor() using
      mode-consistent units; issue #227
[Fix] tlog BASERUN: install.sh replaces default /tmp with $inspath/tmp;
      destructive .gz rotation replaced with read-only zcat pipe
[Fix] find_recentopts incorrectly escaping find options; issue #440, pr#442
[Fix] ignore_file_ext, --exclude-regex, --include-regex, and ignore_paths
      prune: convert to bash arrays for correct find argument passing; empty
 -regex no longer causes find errors; issue #446, #438, #450, #72
[Fix] scan_ignore_user/scan_ignore_group with non-existent user/group no
      longer causes find to error out; issue #335
[Fix] replace ed dependency with tail/cat for log trimming, preserving file
      inode for inotifywait; issue #308
[Fix] get_remote_file(): local variable scoping (svc renamed to grf_svc);
      curl -f flag for HTTP error detection; break replaced with return
[Fix] importconf template: 5 missing variables added, 16 hardcoded values
      changed to $variable expansion, inotify_sleep default corrected,
      Slack scope updated; issue #439
[Fix] scan_strlen() quoting and portability: mktemp, xargs -d '\n',
      while-read loop; checkout() dead code removed, threshold corrected
[Fix] lmdup() remove dead upstreamhash assignment immediately overridden
      by get_remote_file() return value
[Fix] miscellaneous: maldet.sh init script semicolons; replace $RANDOM/$$
      with mktemp; cleanup_scanlist() hardcoded path; cPanel cpapi2
      placeholder; sigup() swapped variable assignments; undefined
      $retry_sleep; ignore_sigs elif to if; inotify_cpulimit reference;
      $intfunc typo; GPL v2 qualifier; "orginal" typo; missing ;; before
      esac; quote critical variable expansions; replace which with
      command -v; compat.conf suppress_cleanhit logic; conf.maldet comment
      typos; email_subj relocated; maldet.sysconfig MONITOR_MODE default;
      scan_stage1() quote $clean_check
[Fix] sigup() guard cp of clean rules with directory existence check to
      prevent error when upstream maldet-cleanv2.tgz contains no clean/ dir
[Fix] chown deprecated '.' separator replaced with POSIX ':' in prerun(),
      clean(), restore_hitlist(), and quarantine(); quote owner:group vars
[Fix] purge() guard inotify_log existence before wc to prevent errors on
      systems where monitoring has never run
[Fix] file_list_et initialized to 0 in -f scan mode so reports show
      correct elapsed time instead of empty value
[Fix] sed -r (GNU-only) replaced with sed -E (POSIX-portable) in cPanel
      contact email extraction and clean() hit name parsing; convert
      backtick to $() on sh_hitname assignment
[Fix] CentOS 6/7 Dockerfiles: isolate optional yara install in subshell
      so required package failures are not swallowed by || true
[Fix] -q/--quarantine, -n/--clean, -s/--restore reject empty SCANID argument
      with clear error message instead of confusing internal errors
[Fix] -f/--file-list background mode: initialize spath/hrspath to file list
      path; fixes empty path in log message and scan report header
[Fix] genalert() digest mode: email_subj permanently mutated by appending
      ": monitor summary", compounding on repeated calls; replaced with
      local digest_subj variable
[Fix] cpulimit comparison: misleading stderr redirect placement
      `[ "$var" -gt 2> /dev/null "0" ]` repositioned to
      `[ "$var" -gt 0 ] 2>/dev/null` in prerun() and monitor_init()
[Fix] scan.etpl ELK integration: bare curl replaced with $curl; for-in-cat
      with IFS abuse replaced with while-read loop; ELK posting extracted
      from column else branch; per-iteration date/hostname forks cached;
      add elk_host/elk_port non-empty validation
[Fix] scan.etpl/panel_alert.etpl: [ "$coltest" ] replaced with
      [ -n "$coltest" ]; UUOC with column replaced with stdin redirect;
      quote all variable paths
[Fix] clamselector(): remove invalid --fdpass from remote clamd TCP path;
      remove redundant --fdpass from remote clamd connectivity test
[Fix] genalert(): add --connect-timeout and --max-time to Slack and Telegram
      curl calls to prevent indefinite hangs on network issues
[Fix] get_remote_file(): remove hardcoded /usr/bin/curl and /usr/bin/wget
      fallbacks; use command-v-discovered variables exclusively
[Fix] hookscan.sh: replace bare pidof with $pidof variable from internals.conf;
      guard for missing pidof binary
[Fix] maldet.sh: add compat.conf sourcing to SysV init script to match standard
      config loading order
[Fix] genalert() panel alerts: temp file cleanup only removed last user's files
      ($sys_user retains final iteration value); replaced with per-user
      cleanup loop; quote all $tmpdir path references in panel alert body
[Fix] storename_prefix: replace $RANDOM (15-bit PRNG) with 32-bit unsigned
      integer from /dev/urandom via od; fallback to epoch timestamp
[Fix] README: scan_cpunice range corrected from (0-19) to (-19 to 19);
      usage_short() add missing --beta to -d|--update-ver display
[Fix] lmdup(): capture install.sh exit code and log output on failure;
      previously discarded all output and continued unconditionally
[Fix] lbreakifs(): remove spurious backspace character from IFS; replace
      echo -en "\n\b" subshell with IFS=$'\n' assignment
[Fix] quarantine_suspend_user(): replace hardcoded /usr/sbin/usermod with
      $usermod variable discovered via command -v; guard for missing binary
[Fix] scan_user_access_minuid: --mkpubpaths fallback default 10 → 100 to
      match internals.conf; add ${:-} guard so conf.maldet value is
      honored; expose variable in conf.maldet and importconf
[Fix] README hookscan section incorrectly stated "native engine only,
      no ClamAV"; hookscan.sh auto-enables ClamAV when clamd is running;
      updated to describe actual auto-detection behavior
[Fix] monitor_check() YARA filtering: capture _yara_filter_filelist()
      return value in both ClamAV and native engine branches; previously
      passed unfiltered file list to scan_stage_yara() causing errors on
      quarantined files (perms 000) and temp file leak per monitor cycle;
[Fix] install.sh: guard SysV registration (update-rc.d, rc-update, chkconfig)
      with systemd check; replace hardcoded chkconfig path with command -v
[Fix] grep without -F on literal file paths in restore_hitlist() and
      clean_hitlist() interpreting regex metacharacters (., *, +, [) as
      pattern syntax; drop useless cat and quote $file
[Fix] monitor_cycle() config reload accumulated ignore_user and
      ignore_group find-filter strings unboundedly without resetting;
      extract shared _build_scan_filters() helper from duplicated code
      in scan() and monitor_cycle()
[Fix] quarantine metadata colon truncation: cut -d: -f9 truncates file
      paths containing colons in .info files and quarantine.hist; changed
      to cut -f9- and awk '{print $NF}' for last-field extraction; also
      fix cut -d: -f2 in quar_hitlist(), restore_hitlist(), clean_hitlist()
      session.hits parsing (4 locations); quote ${file}.info
[Fix] sigignore() permanently deletes lines from on-disk hex.dat and md5v2.dat
      on every scan; signatures irrecoverably lost until next maldet -u; moved
      ignore filtering into gensigs() runtime copies; added runtime_md5 for
      merged MD5 sigs; scan_stage1() reads from runtime_md5
[Fix] view_report() and genalert() type="file" sendmail path prepends SUBJECT:
      header directly into canonical session files, corrupting reports for
      subsequent views; use mktemp staging file instead
[Fix] quote unquoted variable expansions in genalert() ($file, $email_addr,
      $email_panel_from, $email_panel_alert_subj, $contact_emails, $tmpf,
      $email_template, $sessdir paths) and clean() ($cldir command paths);
      prevents word splitting on user-configurable values
[Fix] importconf hardcoded /usr/local/maldetect path replaced with $inspath
      variable
[Fix] scan_days config variable undocumented: add to conf.maldet, importconf,
      man page, and README; used by cron.daily for recent-file scan window
[Fix] JSON injection in ELK and Slack payloads: add _json_escape() helper;
      escape hit_sig and hit_file in scan.etpl ELK curl; escape slack_subj
      in completeUploadExternal JSON body
[Fix] restore_hitlist(): remove unreachable dead-code else branch; collapse
      exhaustive elif to else; move error message to reachable outer
      file-existence check; quote $hitlist on tail
[Fix] scan() days validation: reject zero and negative values with lower-bound
      check; replace subshell grep alpha test with bash [[ =~ ]]
[Fix] escape literal parentheses in ClamAV lstat() ERE filter; unescaped ()
      created empty capture group instead of matching literal parens (2
      locations in _scan_run_clamav and monitor_check)
[Fix] get_remote_file(): remove dead get_return variable (declared, assigned,
      never read); replace || get_return=$? with || true
[Fix] maldet CLI: redirect 4 fatal startup errors (missing config/library
      files) to stderr
[Fix] monitor_check() non-remote clamscan: capture exit code unconditionally
      instead of || clamscan_return=$? which left stale value on success
[Fix] monitor_init() ionice guard missing /proc/vz check present in prerun();
      ionice fails inside OpenVZ containers
[Fix] quar_hitlist() missing chown root:root on quarantined files in non-pub
      branch; quarantine() has the call but quar_hitlist() did not
[Fix] compat.conf: add missing quar_hits → quarantine_hits mapping documented
      in CHANGELOG.VARIABLES; pre-1.5 configs silently lost quarantine_hits value
[Fix] gensigs() temp file leak on repeated calls: monitor_cycle() re-calls
      gensigs on ignore_sigs change, orphaning 7 runtime sig temp files per
      call; add cleanup of previous runtime files before creating new ones
[Fix] _scan_cleanup() missing .hex_md5hits glob; _md5_batch_worker creates
      unused temp file on FreeBSD — move mktemp into Linux branch
[Fix] _hex_compile_pattern() wildcard detection regex accepted uppercase hex
      nibbles but sed conversions only handled lowercase; narrow detection to
      match sed scope (od outputs lowercase); add inline comments to 6
      stderr suppressions in scan engine per coding conventions
[Fix] prerun() sigdir, logdir, tmpdir created with chmod 755 (world-readable);
      tighten to 750 matching sessdir/quardir; quote mkdir/chmod variables;
      install.sh _install_core() adds chmod 750 for sigs/ and logs/
[Fix] genalert() Telegram: bot token visible in /proc/PID/cmdline via inline
      URL argument; use curl -K config file (mktemp, chmod 600) to hide token
      from process listings; temp file removed after curl call
[Fix] CLI argument validation: -c/--checkout, -x/--exclude-regex,
 -i/--include-regex, and --web-proxy now reject missing arguments with
      clear error messages instead of silent no-ops
[Fix] install.sh upgrade: preserve conf.maldet.hookscan (ModSecurity overrides)
      and pub/ per-user state directories; cp -af for pub/ preserves per-user
      ownership
[Fix] purge() inotify_log trim unconditionally when inotify_trim is set; add
      log_size >= inotify_trim guard matching monitor_cycle() behavior
[Fix] checkout() FTP single-file upload: user login sends
      anonymous@rfxn.com@rfxn.com (double domain suffix); variable $user already
      contains full email; remove redundant @rfxn.com append
[Fix] restore() touch -m --date unsupported on FreeBSD; add os_freebsd guard
      using touch -t with date -r epoch conversion
[Fix] genalert() digest mode: cat of missing session.monitor.current on systems
      where monitor has never run; add file existence guard with early return
[Fix] --alert-daily/--monitor-report: add pre-check for running monitor process;
      exits with clear error message when no inotify monitor is active
[Fix] -e/--report: consume optional second argument (email address) to prevent
      it being treated as next CLI option in argument loop
[Fix] install.sh upgrade: guard chattr -ia with command -v; prevents error on
      systems without e2fsprogs (XFS, containers)
[Fix] checkout(): guard ftp binary with command -v; return error with message
      when ftp client is not installed

  -- Changes --
[Change] shared alert_lib updated to v1.0.2: SMTP relay credentials hidden
      from process listing via curl -K config file; webhook URLs redacted in
      error messages; curl -s flag added to email relay for consistency
[Change] panel email delivery uses shared lib _alert_deliver_email with
      command-scoped ALERT_SMTP_FROM and ALERT_EMAIL_REPLY_TO env vars
[Change] ELK statistics JSON escaping uses shared lib _alert_json_escape
[Change] alerting tests updated for shared lib integration; added 3 Discord
      tests (webhook call, disabled state, empty URL guard)
[Change] normalize mixed tabs/spaces to tabs across functions; replace
      if-test default init with parameter expansion in monitor_init()
[Change] sigup() corruption check uses _count_signatures() instead of
      duplicate inline wc -l; restructure elif chain to separate if blocks
[Change] replace ! -z with -n and ! "$x" == "$y" with "$x" != "$y" across
      functions, maldet, scan.etpl, panel_alert.etpl; replace -f && ! -z $(cat)
      with -s for session file existence checks
[Change] eliminate 14x useless cat|cmd pipes in functions; replace with
      direct file arguments, stdin redirects, or read builtins; add grep -h
      on multi-file sig merges to suppress filename prefixes
[Change] deduplicate prerun(): extract _require_bin() helper, replace 5
      dir-creation blocks with loop, 3 sig-file blocks with loop, 2
      default-assign blocks with parameter expansion
[Change] tlog rewritten: shared tlog_lib.sh sourced as in-process library;
      byte-mode tracking for monitor, line-mode for digest email; CLI rewritten
      with option parsing and subcommands; backward-compatible positional interface
[Change] internals.conf: remove orphaned variables — logger (discovered
      but never referenced as $logger), dig, nslookup, remote_ip
      (computed but never used), lmd_verprehook_url, lmd_sigprehook_url
      (URLs defined but never fetched)
[Change] document scan_find_timeout minimum 60-second threshold in
      conf.maldet, importconf, README, and man page; values 1-59 are
      silently treated as disabled
[Change] replace wc -l FILE | awk with wc -l < FILE across 23 locations
[Change] replace 4 subshell grep calls with bash builtins
[Change] extract 10 shared helpers replacing duplicated code blocks:
      _run_yara_scan (4 sites), _send_email (3 sites), _clamscan_fallback (2),
      _build_nice_command (2), _count_signatures (2), _clamd_retry_scan (2),
      _process_clamav_hits (2), _quarantine_file (2), _clean_rescan (2),
      _inotify_trim_log (2)
[Change] quar_get_filestat() rewritten as single-pass IFS=: parser replacing
      9 separate grep|awk/cut pipelines; file_path correctly captures colons
[Change] install.sh: extract _install_core() helper consolidating 13 shared
      operations between fresh install and upgrade paths; eliminate duplicated
      mkdir/chmod/cp/ln/gzip/clamav_linksigs blocks; consolidate clamav_paths
      to single definition
[Change] scan() decomposed from 351 to ~155 lines: temp cleanup centralized
      into _scan_cleanup() (fixes missing cleanup on 2 exit paths), file list
      into _scan_build_filelist(), ClamAV branch into _scan_run_clamav(),
      native branch into _scan_run_native()
[Change] remove Perl dependency for hex scanning; hexfifo.pl and
      hexstring.pl deleted; scan_hexfifo/scan_hexfifo_depth consolidated into
      scan_hexdepth (default 524288); compat.conf migrates old values on upgrade
[Change] rename scan_hex_workers to scan_workers; multi-pass pipeline
      (MD5 → HEX → strlen → YARA); unified progress output with stage
      indicators and running hit counts
[Change] replace egrep with grep -E in clean_hitlist(); update
      usage_long() help text from "POSIX egrep" to "POSIX extended
      regular expression (grep -E)" for --include-regex/--exclude-regex
[Change] convert 22 for-in-cat/backtick anti-patterns to while IFS=
      read -r with process substitution throughout restore_hitlist(),
      clean_hitlist(), quar_hitlist(), scan() ClamAV hit parsing,
      monitor_check() ClamAV/find loops, genalert() panel alerts, prerun_scan()
      ignore/user/group iteration, monitor_cycle() config reload,
      monitor_init() passwd/docroot/file-list/csv/ignore parsing,
      checkout() FTP upload, and gensigs() custom signature processing;
      fixes glob expansion bugs with adversarial filenames and space-
      splitting in unprotected paths
[Change] eliminate ~500,000 fork/exec operations by replacing external
      command pipelines with Bash builtins throughout scan, quarantine,
      monitor, and ClamAV hit paths
[Change] YARA scan refactored: _yara_scan_rules() helper with --scan-list
      batch scanning; _yara_init_cache() caches binary selection
[Change] maldet.service EnvironmentFile changed from conf.maldet to
      /etc/sysconfig/maldet or /etc/default/maldet; ExecStart uses
      ${MONITOR_MODE:-users}; install.sh migrates default_monitor_mode
[Change] convert 7 remaining $$-tempfile paths to mktemp: view_report(),
      scan export filelist, ClamAV scan results, inotify paths, gensigs()
      runtime signatures (3 files)
[Change] cron.daily prune uses find -delete; issue #430
[Change] rewrite usage_short() and usage_long() with categorized sections,
      complete option coverage, --beta flag for -d
[Change] legacy plain-text README replaced with pointer to README.md
[Change] version bump to v2.0.1
[Change] replace 11 bare wc invocations with $wc variable from
      internals.conf for binary path consistency
[Change] view_report() replace for-in-$(ls) with direct glob and
      existence guard; eliminates unnecessary ls subprocess
[Change] convert all backtick command substitutions to $() across functions,
      maldet, and uninstall.sh; unify domain references to rfxn.com
[Change] store regex patterns in variables for [[ =~ ]] matching:
      genalert() hit parsing patterns, prerun() modsec check to glob,
      hookscan.sh metacharacter pattern; per coding conventions
[Change] add local declarations to eout(), restore(), restore_hitlist(),
      clean_hitlist() to prevent global namespace pollution
[Change] internals.conf: add usermod binary discovery via command -v

  -- Documentation --
[Change] man page: add Discord config vars (discord_alert, discord_webhook_url)
      to CONFIGURATION; add alert_lib.sh to FILES; update DESCRIPTION to include
      Discord in alerting channels
[Change] README.md: add discord_alert and discord_webhook_url to Alerting config
      table; add Discord webhook to Alerting & Reporting features list; update
      header description to include Discord
